5#ifndef V8_COMPILER_JS_INLINING_HEURISTIC_H_
6#define V8_COMPILER_JS_INLINING_HEURISTIC_H_
7
8#include "src/compiler/js-inlining.h"
9
10namespace v8 {
11namespace internal {
12namespace compiler {
13
14class JSInliningHeuristic final : public AdvancedReducer {
15 public:
16 enum Mode {
17 kJSOnly, // Inline JS calls only.
18 kWasmWrappersOnly, // Inline wasm wrappers only.
19 kWasmFullInlining, // Inline wasm wrappers and (if supported) whole wasm
20 // functions.
21 };
22
23 JSInliningHeuristic(Editor* editor, Zone* local_zone,
24 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info, JSGraph* jsgraph,
25 JSHeapBroker* broker,
26 SourcePositionTable* source_positions,
27 NodeOriginTable* node_origins, Mode mode,
28 const wasm::WasmModule* wasm_module = nullptr)
29 : AdvancedReducer(editor),
30 inliner_(editor, local_zone, info, jsgraph, broker, source_positions,
31 node_origins, wasm_module, mode == kWasmFullInlining),
32 candidates_(local_zone),
33 seen_(local_zone),
34 source_positions_(source_positions),
35 jsgraph_(jsgraph),
36 broker_(broker),
37 info_(info),
38 mode_(mode),
39 max_inlined_bytecode_size_cumulative_(
40 v8_flags.max_inlined_bytecode_size_cumulative),
41 max_inlined_bytecode_size_absolute_(
42 v8_flags.max_inlined_bytecode_size_absolute) {
43 DCHECK_EQ(mode == kWasmWrappersOnly || mode == kWasmFullInlining,
44 wasm_module != nullptr);
45 }
46
47 const char* reducer_name() const override { return "JSInliningHeuristic"; }
48
49 Reduction Reduce(Node* node) final;
50
51 // Processes the list of candidates gathered while the reducer was running,
52 // and inlines call sites that the heuristic determines to be important.
53 void Finalize() final;
54
55 int total_inlined_bytecode_size() const {
56 return total_inlined_bytecode_size_;
57 }
58
59 private:
60 // This limit currently matches what the old compiler did. We may want to
61 // re-evaluate and come up with a proper limit for TurboFan.
62 static const int kMaxCallPolymorphism = 4;
63
64 struct Candidate {
65 OptionalJSFunctionRef functions[kMaxCallPolymorphism];
66 // In the case of polymorphic inlining, this tells if each of the
67 // functions could be inlined.
68 bool can_inline_function[kMaxCallPolymorphism];
69 // Strong references to bytecode to ensure it is not flushed from SFI
70 // while choosing inlining candidates.
71 OptionalBytecodeArrayRef bytecode[kMaxCallPolymorphism];
72 // TODO(2206): For now polymorphic inlining is treated orthogonally to
73 // inlining based on SharedFunctionInfo. This should be unified and the
74 // above array should be switched to SharedFunctionInfo instead. Currently
75 // we use {num_functions == 1 && functions[0].is_null()} as an indicator.
76 OptionalSharedFunctionInfoRef shared_info;
77 int num_functions;
78 Node* node = nullptr; // The call site at which to inline.
79 CallFrequency frequency; // Relative frequency of this call site.
80 int total_size = 0;
81 };
82
83 // Comparator for candidates.
84 struct CandidateCompare {
85 bool operator()(const Candidate& left, const Candidate& right) const;
86 };
87
88 // Candidates are kept in a sorted set of unique candidates.
89 using Candidates = ZoneSet<Candidate, CandidateCompare>;
90
91 // Dumps candidates to console.
92 void PrintCandidates();
93 Reduction InlineCandidate(Candidate const& candidate, bool small_function);
94 void CreateOrReuseDispatch(Node* node, Node* callee,
95 Candidate const& candidate, Node** if_successes,
96 Node** calls, Node** inputs, int input_count,
97 int* num_calls);
98 bool TryReuseDispatch(Node* node, Node* callee, Node** if_successes,
99 Node** calls, Node** inputs, int input_count,
100 int* num_calls);
101 enum StateCloneMode { kCloneState, kChangeInPlace };
102 FrameState DuplicateFrameStateAndRename(FrameState frame_state, Node* from,
103 Node* to, StateCloneMode mode);
104 Node* DuplicateStateValuesAndRename(Node* state_values, Node* from, Node* to,
105 StateCloneMode mode);
106 Candidate CollectFunctions(Node* node, int functions_size);
107
108 CommonOperatorBuilder* common() const;
109 Graph* graph() const;
110 JSGraph* jsgraph() const { return jsgraph_; }
111 // TODO(neis): Make heap broker a component of JSGraph?
112 JSHeapBroker* broker() const { return broker_; }
113 CompilationDependencies* dependencies() const;
114 Isolate* isolate() const { return jsgraph_->isolate(); }
115 SimplifiedOperatorBuilder* simplified() const;
116 Mode mode() const { return mode_; }
117
118 JSInliner inliner_;
119 Candidates candidates_;
120 ZoneSet<NodeId> seen_;
121 SourcePositionTable* source_positions_;
122 JSGraph* const jsgraph_;
123 JSHeapBroker* const broker_;
124 OptimizedCompilationInfo* info_;
125 int total_inlined_bytecode_size_ = 0;
126 const Mode mode_;
127 const int max_inlined_bytecode_size_cumulative_;
128 const int max_inlined_bytecode_size_absolute_;
129};
130
131} // namespace compiler
132} // namespace internal
133} // namespace v8
